# Competitive Analysis Matrix

Map your product against competitors across key dimensions to find positioning gaps and defensible advantages.

## Config
flow = LR
spacing = 90

## Competitors
- [us] Our Product {icon:🏠} {fill:#89b4fa} {glow}
  The product we're building.
- [c1] Competitor A {icon:🏢} {fill:#cba6f7}
  Describe what they do and who they serve.
- [c2] Competitor B {icon:🏢} {fill:#cba6f7}
  Describe their positioning.
- [c3] Competitor C {icon:🏢} {fill:#cba6f7}
  Often the legacy / incumbent player.

## Core Features
- [f1] Feature 1 {icon:✅} {fill:#a6e3a1} {done}
  Collaboration / sharing
- [f2] Feature 2 {icon:⚙️} {fill:#a6e3a1} {done}
  API / integrations
- [f3] Feature 3 {icon:📱} {fill:#f9e2af} {wip}
  Mobile experience
- [f4] Feature 4 {icon:💰} {fill:#f9e2af}
  Pricing model

## Differentiation
- [d1] We win on… {icon:🏆} {fill:#a6e3a1} {done}
  Speed + simplicity.
- [d2] We lose on… {icon:⚠️} {fill:#f38ba8} {blocked}
  Enterprise security / compliance today.
- [d3] Nobody does… {icon:💡} {fill:#cba6f7} {glow}
  The unmet need — our biggest opportunity.

## Customer Segments
- [seg1] SMB / Startup {icon:🌱} {fill:#f9e2af}
  < 50 employees, fast-moving teams.
- [seg2] Mid-Market {icon:📈} {fill:#89b4fa} {wip}
  50–500 employees, structured workflows.

## Flow
us --> f1: supports
us --> f2: supports
c1 --> f1: supports
c1 --> f2: supports
c2 --> f3: mobile-first
c3 --> f4: complex pricing
f1 --> d1: advantage
f2 --> d1: advantage
f3 --> d2: gap today
d3 --> seg1: targets
d3 --> seg2: targets

## Summary
Competitive Analysis Matrix: map products, features, differentiation, and target segments to find positioning gaps.
